<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="249" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,154,1042]" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,329,909,933]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="249" reason="1">Comments.</emphasis>
The new species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Haliday" baseAuthorityYear="1836" box="[708,793,910,934]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Aptinothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufus">
<emphasis box="[708,793,910,934]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">A. rufus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the shape and the number of antennal segments, and was usually collected along with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Haliday" baseAuthorityYear="1836" box="[461,547,946,970]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Aptinothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufus">
<emphasis box="[461,547,946,970]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">A. rufus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but in smaller numbers. In 
<taxonomicName authority="Alavi, 2020" authorityName="Alavi" authorityYear="2020" box="[846,982,946,969]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Aptinothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iraniensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[846,982,946,969]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">A. iraniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[989,1050,946,970]" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[989,1050,946,970]" pageId="2" pageNumber="249" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
the length of setae S1 on tergite IX is relatively long (vs. very short), and the abdominal tergites II–VIII lack discal setae medially (vs. with). This species is also similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Priesner" authorityYear="1924" box="[309,420,1018,1042]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Aptinothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis box="[309,420,1018,1042]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">A. elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the number of antennal segments, but is separable from that by the key above.
</paragraph>
